CS391 Mininet-based Lab #3: ARP, ICMP, and RIP

Author: Chaofan Lin, 50021911042, ACM Class @SJTU.

To run the mininet:
    $ python ./run_mininet.py [topo_file] -a

To run the POX:
    $ bash ./run_pox.sh

To run the router:
    $ java -jar VirtualNetwork.jar -v [router_name] -r [routing_table] -a [arp_cache]

To test the ICMP implementation:
    Please follow the doc.

To test the ARP implementation:
    $ python ./run_mininet.py [topo_file]
    $ java -jar VirtualNetwork.jar -v [router_name] -r [routing_table]
    (Without the -a argument)

To test the RIP implementation:
    $ java -jar VirtualNetwork.jar -v [router_name]
    (Without the -r argument)

File Structure:
    progAssign3/src/                (source code of the implementation)
    README              (this file)
    Mininet-Lab3-V2.docx   (assignment doc)
